cs.DB, cs.LG, cs.DS, cs.CR, cs.SE 

This paper deals with incremental view maintenance for nested relational databases, which is a topic closely related to database management systems. Therefore, cs.DB (Database) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves formalization, transformation, and semantics-preserving techniques, which are related to machine learning and artificial intelligence, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) the second most likely sub-category. The paper also involves algorithms and data structures, which are related to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The paper also involves security and cryptography, which are related to cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). Finally, the paper involves software engineering techniques, making cs.SE (Software Engineering) a possible sub-category.
